reviews.text: Delicious cold vermicelli and spring rolls. Set lunch very reasonably priced. Huge portion.
Great customer service. Authentic taste. Decent price. Highly recommend

Really bad service.. was really rushed to finish and staff seemed to have a really big problem with me using the loo before we left! To be fair they were closing and wanted to go home, I can understand that.. however when we walked in at 9pm and asked for a table, they should have highlighted that and we would have had that in mind rather than them telling us at 9.45 they were closing and for them then to tell me under breath 'we should have come earlier' when I asked them how to get the bathroom light on (as they'd closed everything down before all customers had left) was super rude! How hard is it to switch the mains on and off?! Other staff arriving food were throwing plates down quite hastily, but used to that in HK. Food was ok.. not the best Vietnamese I've ever had! Had better in London! So go there if you want.. just don't stop them from going home if you don't want to be met with staff with attitude!
You can get a good cheap lunch here, I normally go here with family when trying to save money
An okay Vietnamese restaurant with affordable price.

reviews.text:
A clean and comfortable place.. well equipped, fulfilling all the necessary need during a family's outing.. Very good nursery is also available there.
Surely one will enjoy like anything being there....
Not known the logic behind the name of this place.... Why it is named Olympian ?
... Still searching the answer..........
Decent shopping mall. Have every thing a normal shopping mall has. (Has toys R us and a Tom lee’s music shop)
Good mix of shops and restaurants.

Although, it once was my first time to attend a few of the monthly Recruit job fairs taking place on the underground floor, I think that the big shopping mall center is really decent but as a person who isn't very familiar with and doesn't always go to this location, I've gotten lost in the way to and from here because this area is too humongous to find out how and where to go to. Problems I had encountered in the past was related to its 3 separate phases, which confused me about the directions. "Which way is the correct one to follow?" Somehow, none of those signal boards seem to help me find my way at all. Their signs and arrows are inaccurate information on how or where to go. Guidelines aren't clearly stated above. Misguided me to another phase instead of the phase number that I was trying to figure out to get to. I kept walking around the mall in circles repeatedly and returning to the same exact spot again. This made me feel quite frustrated 😤 because after searching for a long time, I was still unable to reach out to the target of my destination 🎯 "Why would they combine 2 phases together?" I don't know why is it designed like this/ who designed it to be like this, though. Any shopping mall centers should provide us with reliable sources, simply written in excise details that can be easily understood.

Nice place to shop, full of restaurants and the shops are quite affordable. Great selection of international brands. The mall always have some interesting animations going on. Lots of shops for kids as well.

食完晚餐，多令人懷念，可以加到中午餐的用膳地方。

2018 冬
坐位算闊，價錢實惠。生牛肉河一般，豬排飯正常。
服務員誠意推介，加一元有半隻燒雞(聽講因為是 Openrixx 訂位)。以為會貨色麻麻，但意想不到，一蚊雞是整餐晚飯最好食的菜色！多汁，又滑又香。👍🏻
最後是波蘿凍飲，無康怡分店的出色。
吃完了，還有$50 coupon 送，掋食！
